name: Costco butter recalled
summary: Costco has recalled approximately 80,000 pounds of Kirkland Signature unsalted butter due to a labeling error. The affected butter, sold in 24-ounce packages, lacks the required "Contains Milk" statement, posing a potential risk to individuals with milk allergies. The FDA has issued a recall notice, advising consumers to discard any butter that may be affected. Stores across the country, including Texas locations, have been impacted by the recall. The error stems from a printing issue during production, and Costco is cooperating with the supplier to resolve the matter and ensure future products meet labeling requirements.
